A pocket version of "Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs" (SICP) by Abelson, Sussman, and Sussman. With SVG images and properly typeset mathematics. Set in bigger text for comfortable reading on 6" devices.

It is based on Neil Van Dyke's Texinfo version: http://www.neilvandyke.org/sicp-texi/

Official SICP page with HTML version: http://mitpress.mit.edu/sicp/

Thanks Gavrie Philipson (http://github.com/gavrie/sicp-pdf) for the initiative, and others for encouragement!
